BOMB
  Order planes to bomb an enemy or neutral sector, or pin-point a
  specific ship sitting in one.

SYNTAX
  bomb <plane-spec> <target-x,y> [<commodity>]
  bomb <plane-spec> <target-x,y> ship <ship-uid>

DESCRIPTION
  Sends planes on a bombing mission against a target sector. Planes
  fly from wherever they're currently based, and must be within
  range (see 'info fly'/'info wingadd' for how range/fuel work).

  <plane-spec>   - plane uid ("5"), range ("0-5"), comma list ("2,14"),
                   "*" for all eligible planes, "~" for planes with no
                   wing assigned, or a single letter naming a wing
                   (see 'info wingadd' to group planes into a wing)
  <target-x,y>   - the target sector, player-relative coordinates
  <commodity>    - accepted but not yet implemented (see KNOWN GAPS) --
                   bombing always damages the sector's efficiency
  <ship-uid>     - pin-point a specific ship sitting AT <target-x,y>
                   instead of damaging the sector

  Any interceptors based near the target scramble first (see 'info
  fly' for how interception/air combat resolves) -- planes that don't
  survive that pass never reach the target and do no damage.

  Sector bombing: total damage is the sum of surviving planes' bomb
  loads (scaled by their own efficiency) times a random 0.5x-1.5x
  multiplier, applied to the sector's efficiency.

  Ship bombing ('ship <uid>'): same damage formula, but doubled --
  pin-point bombing a single ship is more accurate than carpet-bombing
  a whole sector, matching 4.4.1's precision-bombing bonus. You must
  already know the ship's uid; if you don't, use 'satellite' or
  'recon' with a SPY-flagged plane near it first (a plain 'sat' image
  only shows a shape, not the owner or uid). The ship must currently
  be sitting in <target-x,y> -- if it's moved, the mission fails
  ("not spotted") rather than searching for it elsewhere.

  A submarine can only be pin-pointed by a flight that includes at
  least one ASW-capable plane -- non-ASW planes can't find it at all,
  matching 4.4.1's asw_shipsatxy() gate.

  Planes require at least 40% efficiency to fly, and burn fuel making
  the trip.

KNOWN GAPS (v1)
  - The <commodity> argument is accepted for compatibility but has no
    effect yet -- sector bombing always targets efficiency, never a
    specific stockpiled commodity (4.4.1's 'c' bomb-what mode).
  - No land-unit bombing mode yet (4.4.1's 'l' bomb-what mode).
  - No flak: a targeted ship's own guns don't shoot back at the
    bombers the way a fortress's guns do during 'fire'/navigate
    gauntlet -- see 'info navigate' for the fort gauntlet that DOES
    model return fire.
  - No strategic/nuclear bombing mode (4.4.1's 's' mission distinct
    from 'p' pinpoint) -- this command is 4.4.1's pinpoint bombing
    only.
  - Real 4.4.1 lets you target a sector without knowing what's there
    in advance -- it lists the ships/planes/units present and lets
    you pick interactively. This port requires the ship uid up front
    since empire5 commands don't do multi-step interactive prompts.

EXAMPLE
  bomb * -3,2               all eligible planes bomb sector -3,2
  bomb 0-3 2,4 ship 34       planes 0-3 pin-point bomb ship #34 at 2,4
  bomb c 16,18 ship 21       wing c bombs ship #21 (needs ASW if it's a sub)

